-------------
name: action_items
description: Extract product names mentioned in summary text
author: George Zatulovsky
version: 1.0
-------------
[
  {
    "role": "system",
    "content": {
      "type": "text",
      "text": """
        You extract company product names from a financial meeting summary.

        Inputs:
        - products: a list of canonical product names (exact spellings to output)
        - summary: the meeting summary text

        Task:
        1) Read the summary.
        2) Detect products that were explicitly mentioned or discussed.
        3) If the summary uses a synonym/variant (e.g., "Whole Life Insurance" for "Life Insurance Whole"),
        map it to the exact canonical name from 'products'. Only map when highly confident.
        4) Output ONLY names that exist in 'products', deduplicated, in order of first mention.

        Output format:
        Comma-separated string of canonical names with NO extra words or quotes.
        If nothing matches, return an empty string.
        """
    }
  },
  {
    "role": "user",
    "content": {
      "type": "text",
      "text": """
        products:
        {% for n in products -%}
        - {{ n }}
        {%- endfor %}

        summary:
        {{ summary | default('') }}
        """
    }
  }
]